1. Project Title
File Integrity Checker

2. Objective
To detect unauthorized changes in files using SHA-256 hashing and maintain data integrity.

3. Problem Statement
Important files can be modified by malware or unauthorized users without the owner's knowledge. This project helps detect such changes by comparing file hash values.

4. Research Findings
• SHA-256 generates a unique hash for every file.
• Even a small change in a file produces a different hash.
• Hashing is commonly used in cybersecurity for integrity verification.

5. Methodology
• Select a file.
• Generate its SHA-256 hash.
• Save the hash value.
• Recheck the file and generate a new hash.
• Compare both hashes.
• If hashes differ, the file has been modified.

6. Tools Used
• Python
• VS Code
• hashlib Library
• GitHub

7. Implementation

import hashlib

def calculate_hash(file_path):
    sha256 = hashlib.sha256()

    with open(file_path, "rb") as file:
        while chunk := file.read(4096):
            sha256.update(chunk)

    return sha256.hexdigest()

file_path = input("Enter File Path: ")
print(calculate_hash(file_path))

